fields.name: single_link_node
fields.description: A single link node is a collection of data which also contains one reference point to another node in memory.

fields.name: list-head
fields.description: The head of a list is a property that contains a reference to a piece of data that is to be interpreted as the beginning of that list.

fields.name: list-size
fields.description: List size is an integer value that initializes at 0 and is iterated upwards by 1 for every new value carrying node that is added to the list and iterated downward by 1 for every value carrying node that is removed from the list.

fields.name: list-push
fields.description: Push is a method which adds a node to the end, or tail, of a linked list

fields.name: list-pop
fields.description: Pop is a method which removes the first, or head, item from a linked list and returns it's value.

fields.name: list-peek
fields.description: Peek is a method that returns the value of the front, or head, element of a list without removing it from the list

fields.name: list-is-empty
fields.description: Is Empty is a method which determines whether a linked list has any value bearing elements and returns a boolean.

fields.name: list-tail
fields.description: The tail of a list is a property that contains a pointer to some piece of data that should be treated as the last item in that list.

fields.name: list-enqueue
fields.description: Enqueue adds a new element to the back, or tail, of a First In First Out list.

fields.name: list-dequeue
fields.description: Dequeue removes an element from the front, or head, of a First In First Out list.
